Booty which is given up to the soldiers is either divided or scram- bled for. It may be divided either in the proportion of the pay, or of the deserts of individuals. That it should be divided in proportion to the pay, was the direction of Appius Claudius3 and if he could not carry that, that the money raised from it should be transferred to the treasury.
